<br>
To begin with, every single window now has an unnecessary toolbar over it to tell you what the menu is.  Sorry, but after three years of playing I'm sure I can figure out where to type and where to put my gear.  My chat bar takes up about 25% more room between the toolbar and the fact that the place you type is persistant and doesn't just pop up when you press enter.<br>
<br>
I'm really unimpressed with the new inventory screen too.  I like how everything makes sense where it goes.  Everything for your head goes on the top line (earrings, masks, hats, etc.); everything for your arms on the second line (rins, bracers, sleeves, etc.); everything for the trunk of your body on the third line and finally weapons on the bottom line.  The new interface has the auto-equp box surrounded by your equipment spaces (each with a little picture of what goes in it :rolleyes  ).  <br>
<br>
Not being able to click through windows is also a constant annoyance.  I have my chat screen at the bottom of the screen and in order to loot anything I was constantly having to duck or face down to get the corpse to a place I can loot it.  There isn't a reason that I ever need to click in the chat window to begin with.<br>
<br>
It just seems to me that Verant decided to pick eyecandy over functionality.  When I first logged in on Test I was floored at how amazing it looked, but as soon as I tried to play with it, I was constantly having to struggle with new windows.  Yes, I'll admit a lot of the struggling was due to it being new to me, and I'm sure it will get better over time, but I don't think it is necessary to have little windows for every little thing.  What's the friendlist window for?  It may be unfinished, but right now it serves as a window solely for the /friend and /who all friend command.<br>
<br>
Yes, there are a lot of nice features as well.  As I said, the look is nice.  More icons is nice, and of course the bazaar function will be great.  However, if Verant were to implement this today I'd probably start crying.<br>
<br>
I just pray Verant isn't trying to rush this interface in to disuade people from playing NWN and they are spending the needed time for it.<br>
<br>
Of course, in a few months I bet I'll be astounded by the fact that I actual preferred the old interface.  However, in its current state, it's obviously a work in progress that needs a lot of work (which I don't see Verant denying). <p><div align="Center"><img src="http://members.aol.com/nodnarbjh/csig.jpg" alt="Cantatus - Phantasmist and Artisan of the Karana Server" width="253" height="75">
